description: Prefer stable layout sizes; avoid resize/reflow churn in arcade UI
alwaysApply: true
---

# Stable layout — limit resize

Arcade UI should feel solid. Prefer reserved, equal sizes over content-driven resize that shifts the whole screen.

## Do

- Reserve space for transient UI (verdict, NEXT, hints) so neighbors do not jump when it appears
- Equalize peer controls to the largest needed size for the current state (e.g. answer boxes match the tallest label; center shorter text)
- Use fixed or min heights/widths for chrome that repeats across questions/turns
- Prefer opacity / allowHitTesting toggles over mounting views that change layout height

## Don't

- Let each cell/button size purely to its own text when peers share a row/grid
- Grow/shrink primary play areas when secondary copy (CORRECT/INCORRECT, hints) appears
- Animate layout size changes for routine state (answered, focus, streak) — animate color/opacity/scale on a stable frame instead

## Example

```swift
// ❌ Each choice sizes to its own label — grid reflows every question
Text(label).padding().background(...)

// ✅ Measure once per question; all boxes share max height; text centered
Text(label)
  .frame(maxWidth: .infinity, maxHeight: .infinity, alignment: .center)
  .frame(minHeight: uniformHeight)
```
